{"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Class","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPolyline","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MLNPolyline","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"class","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNPolyline","role":"symbol","title":"MLNPolyline"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Type Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline\/polylineWithCoordinates:count:"],"anchor":"Type-Methods","generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@interface","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNPolyline","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)MLNMultiPoint","text":"MLNMultiPoint","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can add polyline shapes to the map by adding them to an "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object. Configure the appearance of an "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"’s or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"’s polylines collectively using an "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNLineStyleLayer","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object. To access a polyline’s attributes, use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolylineFeature","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, you can add a polyline overlay directly to a map view using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addOverlay:","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" methods. Configure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a polyline overlay’s appearance using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:lineWidthForPolylineAnnotation:","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"them. The first and last vertices are not connected to each other, but you can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specify the same "},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as the first and last vertices in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"order to close the polyline. To fill the space within the shape, use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentatio